# Normalize line endings: LF in the repo for all text files, regardless of OS.
* text=auto eol=lf

# ...except Windows batch files, which cmd.exe must get with CRLF. cmd seeks
# through a .cmd by BYTE offset while counting CHARACTERS, so with LF endings
# any multi-byte UTF-8 character (an em-dash in a comment is enough) drifts the
# parser and it resumes mid-line, executing fragments of its own comments. CRLF
# resynchronises it. Without this rule a fresh checkout gets LF and the
# launcher silently mis-parses. Keep the launcher's contents ASCII-only too —
# belt and braces, since the two faults only bite in combination.
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.bat text eol=crlf

# Binary assets (none yet, but future-proof the convention).
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
